article.headline: San Diego 74, Point Loma 51
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Gyno Pomare scored 19 points as San Diego beat Pt. Loma Nazarene 74-51 on Thursday night. The Toreros increased their lead to 31-9 with 5:19 left in the first half to pull away from their crosstown NAIA opponent. San Diego (2-1), which held a 44-19 halftime lead, limited the Sea Lions to 21.9 percent (7-for-32) shooting from the floor in the first half. Josh Sanderson scored 15 points to lead Pt. Loma Nazarene (3-0), which played the game as an exhibition so it did not count on its record. Pomare also had 10 rebounds and Theo White added nine. San Diego lost starting center Nir Cohen earlier in the day when he suffered a broken arm in the team's shootaround. Cohen is expected to miss four weeks.
